sec.p:
In this paper it is considered that the linear parts of the system, i.e. M and K, are fully known and ϕ is a parameter belonging to the nonlinear restoring force fNL(y,y·). Therefore, one may obtain the sensitivity of the FRF between coordinates p and q, i.e. Hpq(ωk), as follows:
(17)∂Hpq(ωk)∂ϕ=-{Hpa(ωk)}(∂k¯(Yk,ωk)∂ϕ[Γ]){Hqa(ωk)}
where {Hpa(ωk)}T and {Hqa(ωk)} are pth row and qth column vectors of analytical frequency response matrix. Equation (17) states that the sensitivity of the FRF depends on the sensitivity of the equivalent linear model to the parameters of the nonlinear restoring force, i.e. ϕ. At this point we consider that this sensitivity is known. Calculation of this quantity is explained later in this paper.
